                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.2311/51.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of Texas</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin, Tex.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have no objections to movement of Mexican troops through Texas territory as
                    requested, with proper safeguards.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">O. B. Colquitt.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
